      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: close readline interface and destroy read stream in transcript store",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes a file descriptor leak in `TranscriptsStore.readUtterancesFromDir`. The `createReadStream` and `readline.createInterface` were not cleaned up after use. If `JSON.parse` threw inside the async iteration loop, the underlying file descriptor would remain open indefinitely.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nWrap the `for await` loop in a `try/finally` block that explicitly calls `lines.close()` and `stream.destroy()`.\n\n## User Impact\n\nNo user-visible change. Prevents file descriptor exhaustion when reading large or malformed transcript files.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- **`src/agents/tools/transcripts-tool.test.ts`: all tests pass** ✅\n- **`src/commands/sessions-tail.test.ts`: all tests pass**\n- Node.js `readline` docs: `createInterface` does not close the underlying stream; explicit `close()` + `destroy()` is the recommended pattern",
        "branch": "fix/readline-stream-leak",
